==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cerotin
<hw>Cer"o*tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Cerotene</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
substance, <chform>C27H55.OH</chform>, obtained from Chinese wax, and
regarded as an alcohol of the paraffin series; -- called also
<altname>cerotic alcohol</altname>, <altname>ceryl
alcohol</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerotype</ent>⟦br⟧
